<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><!DOCTYPE topic  PUBLIC '-//OASIS//DTD DITA Topic//EN'  'topic.dtd'><topic id="GUID_83CC164E-ECED-4A9E-8AD7-C16D1E856C53"><title>ESD Diode Selection</title><body><section id="SECTION_E6A0BC37-402C-4C9E-A03C-8A1F8115E4FD"><p>ESD diode selection recommendations below only apply to interfaces with:</p><ul><li><p>Hotplug input/output port application (external ports that exposed to end user)</p></li><li><p>Direct connection between SOC and connector (Eg, without redriver / retimer in between)</p></li></ul><p>For interfaces that require retimer:</p><ul><li><p>Intel retimer: Refer to Thunderbolt retimer or controller documentation for more details, document number can be found in PDG chapter “EMC/RF Reference Documents”.</p></li><li><p>Third party retimer: Customer may contact vendor for necessary ESD protection.</p></li></ul><p>For further ESD design optimization, customers may refer to Chapter “System Efficient ESD Design (SEED)” for more details.</p><table id="TABLE_E6A0BC37-402C-4C9E-A03C-8A1F8115E4FD_1" scale="60"><title>Discrete ESD Protection Diode Selection Guidelines</title><tgroup cols="6"><thead><row valign="top"><entry outputclass="rotate90">Interface</entry><entry outputclass="rotate90">Data Rate</entry><entry outputclass="rotate90"> ESD Diode Placement</entry><entry outputclass="rotate90">ESD Diode Shunt Capacitance</entry><entry outputclass="rotate90">ESD Diode Rdyn</entry><entry outputclass="rotate90">ESD Diode Reverse Working Voltage</entry></row></thead><tbody><row><entry><p>HDMI 2.1 Direct Connect Rate ≤ 6 Gbps (Data)</p></entry><entry><p>≤ 6 Gbps  </p></entry><entry><p>&lt; 25 mm routing length from connector  </p></entry><entry><p>&lt; 0.4 pF  </p></entry><entry><p>&lt; 0.5 Ohm  </p></entry><entry><p>4.0 V </p></entry></row><row><entry><p>HDMI 2.1 Direct Connect Rate &gt; 6Gbps (Data)</p></entry><entry><p>&gt; 6 Gbps  </p></entry><entry><p>&lt; 25 mm routing length from connector  </p></entry><entry><p>&lt; 0.4 pF